  "reveal": {
    "brief_voiced": "Zane Swain stands as the killer. The protocol demands an unloaded pistol at the place beside any lady; Effie Strange sat beside Nan Pringle's seat at the fourth position on the host's right, yet that pistol lay charged. Zane Swain occupied the fifth place on the right, directly across from Lady Lavinia Loveless at the fifth place on the left, and that charged pistol at the fourth place fell within his reach. He took it and fired across the table.\n\nZane Swain, by all accounts, was fond of the rules—correct in all things, devoted to protocol. Yet Lady Lavinia Loveless, a woman apt to let people rather too close, had allowed herself a liberty he could not forgive. A footman's care for order, wounded by a lady's careless breach of it, became his motive.\n\nThe file closes on a servant who loved the rules too well.",
